------------------------------------------------------------------------
SCUM -- graphical user interface server
------------------------------------------------------------------------

SCUM is a graphical user interface server that can be controlled from
any client program via OSC.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
requirements
------------------------------------------------------------------------

* fltk 1.1
* opengl

------------------------------------------------------------------------
compilation
------------------------------------------------------------------------

compilation boils down to the usual

$ ./configure && make && make install

you need fltk 1.1 which ships with an fltk-config script. if this
script is not in your PATH, you can point the configure script to its
location with the --with-fltk-config option.

fltk needs to be built with opengl support, which is the case in most
distributions. on debian/unstable you can apt-get install
libfltk1.1-dev and should be set.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
usage (linux)
------------------------------------------------------------------------

the lib subdirectory in the distribution needs to be included in
sclang's library configuration, by adding a line like the following to
~/.sclang.cfg:

+$HOME/path/to/sclangx/lib

in order to access the online help files, either copy the help
subdirectory to the directory where you keep the SuperCollider help
files or just make a symbolic link.

in order to use sclangx from emacs, customize the variable
sclang-program, e.g.:

(setq sclang-program "sclangx")

------------------------------------------------------------------------
usage (osx)
------------------------------------------------------------------------

put the lib and help subdirectories where the compiler can find it:

ln -s /path/to/scum-src ~/Library/Application\ Support/SuperCollider/Extensions/SCUM

------------------------------------------------------------------------
examples
------------------------------------------------------------------------

nothing much yet, have a look at the help files and the implementation
of ServerWindow/ServerPanel.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
disclaimer
------------------------------------------------------------------------

the GUI classes are far from complete, but they provide a decent
overview of what might be possible.

--
EOF
